result.execSummary:
All charges against Timothy Alan Griffin in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Timothy Alan Griffin is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Timothy Alan Griffin appeared by video.  Attorney Mark Walter Frank appeared by video for Timothy Alan Griffin.  Attorney Lisa A. Riniker in court for State of Wisconsin. DA Riniker heard. Illinois warrant canceled. State moves to dismiss extradition. State advises there is a pending warrant in Iowa defendant should address. Attorney Frank heard. Case dismissed.

Defendant Timothy Alan Griffin appeared by video.  Attorney Mark Walter Frank in court for Timothy Alan Griffin.  Attorney Lisa A. Riniker in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Frank heard and defendant is suppose to meet with his Dubuque Probation Agent today. Attorney Frank has verified with Jo Daviess County that the warrant is valid with full extradition. Attorney Frank has advised defendant to turn himself in after seeing his Dubuque County Probation Agent. Defendant heard and indicated that he plans to turn himself. Court heard. Extradition hearing set.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Timothy Alan Griffin appeared by phone.  Attorney Lisa A. Riniker in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant qualifies for SPD but counsel has not been assigned yet. State heard. Defendant is on probation with Illinois. Per Agent Dickman of DOC in Wisconsin, defendant failed to meet with probation agent. Warrant is valid. Court advises defendant to contact agent in Illinois to resolve issue. Call SPD with next court date also. State provides contact information for DOC agent in Illinois. Extradition hearing continued.
Extradition hearing scheduled for July 14, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Extradition hearing on July 14, 2022 at 10:30 am.

Timothy Griffin appears in court, in custody at Grant County Jail. Attorney Lisa Riniker appears in court. Attorney Riniker swears to extradition complaint. Court explains complaint, extradition rights, and right to counsel. Defendant heard. State heard and requests a cash bond. Court heard and orders $50 cash bond. Extradition hearing set.
Extradition hearing on June 20, 2022 at 11:00 am.
